videoframeSigmonVm0006MIB.description: This MIB describes the device specific objects of the VM0006 GPI Interface Module, and augments MIB-2, VF-GENERIC, and VF-SIGMON in the identification of this Videoframe Systems managed device. This module will be extended or modified as required. Videoframe Systems reserves the right to make changes in specification and other information contained in this document without prior notice. vm0006Table.name: vm0006Table
vm0006Table.description: Each row contains information about one VM0006 GPI Interface module in the managed VF200 frame.

vm0006SlotNumber.name: vm0006SlotNumber
vm0006SlotNumber.description: The slot that this entry represents.

vm0006Active.name: vm0006Active
vm0006Active.description: Indicates whether this entry is active (this module is in this slot).

vm0006Locate.name: vm0006Locate
vm0006Locate.description: Controls the locate indicator on the module and indicates its current state. Set to flash (1) to cause the locate LED on the front of the module to begin flashing. Set to off to stop flashing.

vm0006GPISignalTable.name: vm0006GPISignalTable
vm0006GPISignalTable.description: Each row contains information about one GPI signal of one VM0006 GPI Interface module in the managed VF200 frame.

vm0006GPISignalEntry.name: vm0006GPISignalEntry
vm0006GPISignalEntry.description: A GPI Interface module GPI signal entry.

vm0006GPISignalSlotNumber.name: vm0006GPISignalSlotNumber
vm0006GPISignalSlotNumber.description: The frame slot number that this entry represents.

vm0006GPISignalNumber.name: vm0006GPISignalNumber
vm0006GPISignalNumber.description: The GPI number within the module.

vm0006GPISignalState.name: vm0006GPISignalState
vm0006GPISignalState.description: Indicates the current state of this GPI signal.

vm0007GPIChandedAck.name: vm0007GPIChandedAck
vm0007GPIChandedAck.description: When Auto Re-Arm is set to off, set to acknowledge (3) to acknowledge a triggered gpiChanged notification.

vm0006GPISignalName.name: vm0006GPISignalName
vm0006GPISignalName.description: The name of this GPI signal.

vm0006GPISignalDescription.name: vm0006GPISignalDescription
vm0006GPISignalDescription.description: Descriptive identification of this GPI signal.

vm0006GPISignalTrapEnable.name: vm0006GPISignalTrapEnable
vm0006GPISignalTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables trap generation from this GPI signal.

gpiChanged.name: gpiChanged
gpiChanged.description: One or more GPIs, for which traps are enabled, has changed state.
